// INSTRUCTIONS: I am trying to filter out empty arrays from an array. In other words, I want to transform something that looks like this: ["a", "b", [], [], [1, 2, 3]] to look like ["a", "b", [1, 2, 3]]. My code looks like this:

// function removeEmptyArrays(arr) {
//   return arr.filter(x => x !== [])
// }

// However, somehow, the empty arrays still exist. Fix this incorrect code to remove the empty arrays.

function removeEmptyArrays(arr) {
	return arr.filter(x => x.length !== 0);
}